  "text": "Genotyping was done as described previously [CITATION_1] ). Genomic DNA was extracted and purified from tail clippings using a commercial kit (QIAGEN), and 2 l was diluted in 50 l of PCR master mix (Roche Diagnostics). PCR was performed using a forward primer from the receptor sequence (5 Ј -CACCTGCCCTGCTACAGGAAGAG-3 Ј ; nucleotides 423-445 from GenBank/EMBL/DDBJ under accession no. U22409) and a reverse primer from the pcDNA1 vector in the transgene (5 Ј -TTC-CACCACTGCCTCCCATTCATC-3 Ј ). The samples were heated at 94 Њ C for 1 min; and 30 cycles were performed at 94 Њ C for 30 s, 58 Њ C for 45 s, 72 Њ C for 1 min, and 72 Њ C for 3 min for termination. PCR products resolved by electrophoresis yielded a 350-bp product present only from genomic DNA from tg mice.",
